184
00:11:31,219 --> 00:11:36,806
ITER at the end of its lifetime
will only reach a few dpa.

185
00:11:36,806 --> 00:11:39,956
So this is really a completely 
different situation,

186
00:11:39,956 --> 00:11:44,622
that of an actual fusion reactor,
much, much higher radiation

187
00:11:44,622 --> 00:11:48,904
of neutrons and therefore
much, much more severe effects.

188
00:11:49,384 --> 00:11:52,495
In terms of the creation
of helium and hydrogen

189
00:11:52,495 --> 00:11:55,035
in the reactor of that kind
