191
00:12:00,755 --> 00:12:03,760
We notice of course that dpa's
and appm's are related

192
00:12:03,760 --> 00:12:08,508
which complicates the dynamics
of the whole process,

193
00:12:08,508 --> 00:12:11,212
or the whole set of processes

194
00:12:11,642 --> 00:12:17,692
and also makes it difficult to really
calculate and simulate <i>a priori</i>

195
00:12:17,692 --> 00:12:19,473
what the effects can be.

196
00:12:19,473 --> 00:12:22,439
I also notice that these ratios
of appm's to dpa's

197
00:12:22,439 --> 00:12:25,906
are much higher in fusion
than in fission.

198
00:12:26,946 --> 00:12:29,602
So in terms of the macroscopic
material properties

199
00:12:29,602 --> 00:12:34,382
the 14 MeV neutrons will change,
first of all, the chemical composition,

200
00:12:34,382 --> 00:12:36,899
will change the physical properties
of the material,

201
00:12:36,899 --> 00:12:41,392
this is very important for material
that has to perform a certain function.

202
00:12:41,392 --> 00:12:44,766
For example, the electrical conductivity
will be decreased

203
00:12:44,766 --> 00:12:48,301
as well as the thermal conductivity,
typically for surrounding materials.

204
00:12:48,301 --> 00:12:52,764
So this is something to be aware of
when designing pieces

205
00:12:52,764 --> 00:12:56,994
that have to accomplish
a particular function in the reaction.

206
00:12:58,394 --> 00:13:02,780
At least as importantly,
the flux of 14 MeV neutrons

207
00:13:02,780 --> 00:13:05,067
will also influence mechanical properties.

208
00:13:05,067 --> 00:13:08,040
This is very important
